<br>
The pointers provided say to shout or auction that you are looking for a heart and you might get to loot one. This doesn't work so well because I play on a Team PvP server and there aren't more than 9 people in Perma that I've seen and usually it's me and one or two more.<br>
<br>
It also says that the Heart of Frost will drop on different MoBs in there. Has anyone seen that? I've cleared the preacher's room multiple times and have NEVER had a Wizzie spawn there. I've killed plenty of Evokers. It's tough to move deeper inside to look because the little green buggers aggro the hell out of me!<br>
<br>
Thx for any input<br>
<br>
Totenkopf<br>
<br>
What other MoBs will this drop from? <p><center><br>"Aces high, baby, and you just drew the death card!"<br>
<img src="http://www.geocities.com/bennythetorch/Toten1.jpg" width="70" height="85" border="0"</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/01 11:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another Temperate Flux question</span><hr size=1> I've never seen them by the preacher either. The area by the frozen king is more likely, and you can stop by and get wolfie slippers while you're at it. <p><b>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unygex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nygeX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/01 12:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What I Did</span><hr size=1> I waited awhile before doing this quest so have somewhat recent experience getting the heart in Perma.  When I went there was only one other player in the zone.  He was a level 41 shaman and informed me he did single pulls from a group because of his level.  This was invaluable info, me being level 48 at the time, because I was trying to figure out how to pull the lone wizard standing up on a rock without having the whole room aggro.  <br>
<br>
When you go into Perma invis and head towards the King room (go right at the flag room) and you will come to a large gate.  Take a left after entering the gate and there is a small gate that opens up into a large room.  I killed the lone gobs standing around the gates with one conflag and then spotted the wizard standing on a rock in the large room.  I popped him with a level 12 shock of lightning and then backed up back into the gate to wait for him.  He finally showed up and I dropped him and he had the heart.  Maybe I just got lucky but it was pretty simple actually. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unygex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nygeX</A> at: 2/5/01 10:03:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utotenkopftz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TotenkopfTZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/01 12:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What I Did</span><hr size=1> thx for the input...I'll give it a try.<br>
<br>
I'm in my mid 30s and the little greenies don't want to leave me be...but King's room it is!<br>
<br>
Totnekopf <p><center><br><font size = 2><font color=yellow><b>"You play for Good...I play for keeps."</font></font></b><br>
<img src="http://www.geocities.com/bennythetorch/Toten1.jpg" width="70" height="85" border="0"</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulordbug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordBug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/01 2:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What I Did</span><hr size=1> The heart is off wizards, AND ONLY wizards.  This holds true for both hearts.  The heart of frost I got on my first wizard kill (preacher room), the heart of fire took forever.  Finally got it after about 10 wizard kills by the bar.<br>
<br>
&quot;The frozen king&quot; you mentioned is the Scryer room.  Good place to set up camp.  Breaking the room can be tricky (8 gobos, usually casters), but holding it after that shouldn't be hard (respawn of 20+ minutes).  The only time I broke the room, I was 45 and had a 40 warrior with me.  Long fight, don't let anything run.  Can probably pick up an ice crystal staff and wolf fur slippers while you're there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufazzno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fazzno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/01 2:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What I Did</span><hr size=1> Just got the staff over the weekend<br>
<br>
Heart of frost : Perma in Preacher room. Kind shaman was camping it and said for me to come loot it. It was off an ice goblin wizard.<br>
<br>
Heart of fire : Killed several fire gob wizards near bar room and couldn't find it. Finally hung around the Sol B zone line and waited for a group to pull trains from the bar area. Looted one off a fire gob wiz after about the 5th or 6th one.<br>
<br>
Rod of bone - easily solo'ed when I was 49 or 50<br>
<br>
Lambent stone off hg's/sg's = staff of ro or darkwood staff.<br>
<br>
Once you get this staff, you can kite to your heart's content and never have to look back to judge distances. It's also great for pulling green trains on yourself to clear yard trash - SRO comes to mind for the AC.<br>
<br>
Good luck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvryk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vryk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/01 8:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What I Did</span><hr size=1> When I got my ice heart it was from a wizard in the king room.  Later that same night (we decided to pharm the area just for fun since we were there LOL) a second heart dropped from one of the named (not the king) that spawns near the king.  I wish I could remember who it was but it was NOT, I repeat NOT a wizard.<br>
<br>
PS Thunderclap is loads of fun in that room, wish I'd had Supernova at the time! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><font size=3>- <b>Vryk Deikana</b><br>
<font size=2>       <i>49 Wizard, Prexus</i><br>
<font size=1>          <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=11317" target="_top">view profile</a>
</font size></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uattreau.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Attreau</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/01 2:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Named</span><hr size=1> The named you are speaking of is : The Warlock<br>
<br>
I've kill the Warlock several times, never gotten anything special, but he dropps both the Snowball and Heart of Ice, just like the Wizards.<br>
<br>
-Att <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvoltaeus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Voltaeus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/8/01 2:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reply</span><hr size=1> The Heart of FRost drops off more things than wizards, I got mine off some other MoB.  Head to the King room.  I swear that the Heart drops every 15-30 minutes there if you clear it.<br>
<br>
Voltaeus Visionseeker<br>
Wizard of the 27th Season <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aelina>Aelina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/8/01 4:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> I could be wrong but I think the heart of fire drops from the inferno goblin wizards and not the fire goblin wizards.  I just know for sure that I got my heart of fire off the first inferno goblin wizard I killed and had not gotten anything off many fire goblin wizards. <p><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>Aelina</td></tr>
<tr><td>Wizard of Neriak</td></tr>
<tr><td>Follower of The Burning Prince</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ayonae Ro</td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/8/01 9:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> I got luckyon my heart of frost:  I weas finishing the staff of the wheel quest and decided to get my heart while I was on that end of the world.  Ran in invis, got lucky and found a wizard that I could kill solo, nailed him and got my heart.<br>
<br>
The heart of fire was another matter, I stopped into Sol off and on from level 27 to 35 and didn't get it until some troll who was being power leveled trained it to me.  Go figure, hehe<br>
<br>
Both hearts came off of Wizards, the heart of fire came from an Inferno Goblin Wizard<br>
<br>
Good luck, this staff rocks!  It drops flame shields on mobs too  :) <p><P></P>
